- Update to version 6.4.1:
  * New function vegas.restratify(integ, f) creates a copy of
    integrator integ but with a new y-space stratification that is
    adapted to integrand f(x).
  * New vegas.Integrator option correlate_integrals if True
    (default) instructs vegas to evaluate correlations between the
    different integrals when integrating multiple integrands at
    the same time.
  * Bugs are fixed for pickling objects of type vegas.RAvgDict
    (for Python 3.14), and for vegas.Integrator(integ) where integ
    is an integrator.

